Some clarity (or experimentaion on category D personel...) needed here I think


21 Mar 2010 09:14






This article falls into the old error of categorising Christians as either Roman Catholics or Protestants. Where do Anglicans (either protestants who pre-date the protestant movement and where hostile to it (hence the UK monarch's title of "Defender of the Faith") or Catholics who engaged in Protestation, depending who you ask) fall on this scale? Roman Catholicism is not a synonym of Catholicism.

This is complicated by the article itself that seems to have taken a stance, without actually proving it. If it was inteded for Elizabeth then the opening part shoudl drop the "ie any Protestant Denomination" bit.

Otherwise a really cool SCP, got my Upvote.





